reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple, Functional and Classy Looking
reviews.reviewText: I was on the hunt for bedside tables that won't allow *some* people to clutter the top and fill the drawers with junk and detritus from pockets. I was also looking for a lamp. I found these!Feature by feature: The top shelf has a rest that holds a cell phone, tablet or other slim device, along with two USB ports (standard and whatever that new one is called), plus an outlet. Handy-dandy, with no room for clutter. The middle shelf is just the right size for a water bottle, lotion and maybe some small items--again, not much opportunity for clutter. The bottom shelf is at floor level, so maybe a decorative plant or a stack of books. Or leave it clear. (Mr. Clutter set his C-Pap machine on the second shelf--perfect fit.)The lamp itself has a plastic/paper surround that diffuses light nicely. It looks very nice. I wouldn't say it's good for nighttime reading, but small reading lamps are inexpensive and easy to find. So no big deal. I really like that it has a chain pull to turn on and off. Easy to find and reach from bed, even in the dark.Assembly was a breeze. It's put together nicely. Mr. Clutter put together one; I put together the other. The instructions are easy to follow.I have a small issue with the stability. It's not exactly top-heavy, but I wouldn't have it around rowdy children or pets. Not that it falling would cause serious harm, since it's not heavy, but it could be damaged. So make sure it's placed on flat carpet or an even floor.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality easy to build
reviews.reviewText: This is the third one of these lamps I have purchased. They are built well. All the parts are there and fit perfectly. No tools required. Took me 10 minutes or so per lamp. I like the style. I like the 2 USB and one outlet in it and the shelves. Very pleased with my purchase!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute but flimsy
reviews.reviewText: This is cute and nifty, fits perfectly in the corner of my room. It is however pretty flimsy/not sturdy, but you get what you pay for. Building it was easy and not at all time consuming. I love that it has the outlet (seems lose when anything is connected) and USB ports.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Not sturdy, but beautiful and functional
reviews.reviewText: One of the most aesthetic lamps I came across! The light fades perfectly through the fabric and the square design is also very appealing. For that price, it's a perfect buy. Sturdiness isn't great on thick carpers tho.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Could not imagine 2 lamps in such a small box!
reviews.reviewText: Fairly easy to assemble however instructions had letters on parts but atual parts were not lettered. Did not understand the wifi instructions at all so I left that part out. When I flipped the switch on them, widlfi worked much to my surprise!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks great but feels cheap.
reviews.reviewText: So I decided not to ding the stars on the product because it was on sale and I feel like i got a fantastic deal. Its easy enough to put together and I like the way it looks. It does not feel structurally sound. If anyone or anything put some weight on it I feel like it would snap. But at this price and for what I need it for I love it. Made the perfect router/modem stand with a nice charger port. Highly recommended!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great lamp, but…
reviews.reviewText: The lamp is great. Easy to put together! The only complaint is that there is a small crack on the shade, which will probably get bigger overtime.
